:R-HSA-425561  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0070588 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Calcium ions are used by cells as ubiquitous signalling molecules that control diverse physiological events. Three mammalian gene families control Ca2+ transport across plasma membranes and intracellular compartments (Lytton J, 2007). They are the Na+/Ca2+ exchanger family designated NCX (SLC8) (three members NCX1-3) (Quednau BD et al, 2004), the Na+/Ca2+-K+ exchanger family designated NCKX (SLC24) (five members NCKX1-5) (Schnetkamp PP, 2004) and a Ca2+/cation exchanger (NCKX6, NCLX) whose physiological function remains unclear." ;
        rdfs:label          "Sodium/Calcium exchangers" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: Jassal, Bijay, 2009-06-05" , "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2009-06-05" , "Reviewed: He, L, 2009-08-24" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-425561" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-425410/R-HSA-425410> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

